dsl

Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • dsl.Node
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    EnactNode, EndNode, RootNode, RunNode, SendNode, TestNode

    abstract class Node
extends java.lang.Object
    This class models one unit of code in the centralized description of the protocol. It is sub-classed for each type of action a character can take in the description (whether a send, a run or a test).
    Author:
    rongomai

    • Field Detail

      • character

        protected java.lang.String character
        The identifier of the character performing the action described in this node.

      • nextAction

        protected java.lang.Object nextAction
        The next action for the character to execute after this. If it is null, action proceeds normally, if it is a Node, execution jumps to this node and if it is a set of messages, execution halts and waits for one of the listed messages to arrive.
        See Also:
        Part

      • put

        public abstract void put(Node to,
                         Outcome outcome)
        Creates an edge from this node to the "to" node, with type given by the outcome provided. The outcome must be valid for the node type.
        Parameters:
        to - the "to" node of the edge created.
        outcome - the outcome which takes execution from the current node to the next one.

      • next

        public abstract Node next(Actor<?> actor)
        Executes the action described in this node, using the Actor object provided and returning the next node in the execution path.
        Parameters:
        actor - the actor on which the action described in this node will be performed.
        Returns:
        the next node to be executed by the actor.

      • quickCheck

        public abstract void quickCheck()
        Performs a quick (and incomplete) sanity check of the adjacencies. To be replaced in the future for more efficient code.

      • isActiveFor

        public boolean isActiveFor(java.lang.String characterName)
        Checks if the identifier given equals the identifier of this node.
        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • getCharacter

      • getNextAction

        public final java.lang.Object getNextAction()
        Gets the next action that the Actor class has to execute after this Node. It can be a BitSet indicating a set of initial messages to be received or a next active Node to be executed or null, in case the next node is indeed the next Node directly under it.
        Returns:
        a reference to the next action. It still needs to be casted.

      • setNextAction

        public final void setNextAction(java.lang.Object nextAction)

        Parameters:

        for a fuller explanation.

      • enqueueAdjs

        public final void enqueueAdjs(java.util.List<Node> queue)
        Enqueues all adjacencies from a node, except those reached by Outcome.NO_RECEIVE, which are always to be treated as a separate case in searches.
        Parameters:
        queue - a queue used in a BSF search.

      • mapEnds

        public final void mapEnds(Node next,
                          Node noSend,
                          Node noReceive)
        Substitutes all EndNode for the corresponding given nodes. This is used to integrate one flowchart into another.
        Parameters:
        next - the node to which to go instead of EndNode.OK.
        noSend - the node to which to go instead of EndNode.NO_SEND.
        noReceive - the node to which to go instead of EndNode.NO_RECEIVE.
